title: Strike Data with a Crisis Point.
author-name: Lieberman, O.
Author-X-Name-Last: Lieberman
Author-X-Name-First: O.
keywords: STATISTICS ; STRIKES
length: 15 pages
abstract: The paper is concerned with the analysis of strike data in which the 
    distribution of short strikes differs from that of long strikes. It appears 
    through visual inspection and asymptotic prodecures that for Israeli strikers 
    in the years 1965-1992, the hazard function is exponential for strikes lasting 
    less than 40 days and that it is Weibull with a Weibull parameter greater than 
    unity for longer strikes.
